{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"858bb456-6c93-4f97-8612-3e9e6e37b6d8","content":"There's no existing pipeline in this directory, so here's a general migration guide.\n\n## Migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test project\n\nIn your `.csproj`, add:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nEnsure you're on **MSTest 3.x+** (the SDK-style package):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.7.3\" />\n```\n\n### 2. Replace VSTest@3 with `dotnet test`\n\n**Before:**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    resultsFolder: $(Agent.TempDirectory)\\TestResults\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After:**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=TestResults.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `vstest.console.exe` | Test host is the exe itself |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--logger trx` |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` |\n| Publishing | Automatic | Needs `PublishTestResults@2` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |\n\n### 3. For Cobertura output (recommended)\n\nAdd the `coverlet.collector` package and use:\n```\n--collect:\"XPlat Code Coverage\"\n```\nThis produces `.cobertura.xml` directly, which `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` consumes natively.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"837d893e-e206-4450-b054-9d984a825d8d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. This is a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure Pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":689,"requestId":"0830:1DCDBF:7D29B22:8B65989:69EABE78"},"id":"b71f73bd-8c25-43c4-a9e0-68dac4777711","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:51:16.873Z","parentId":"0c72f398-64a1-4ee2-b120-4b0a52a7cb73"}
